            <div class="reveal">
                <h2>What I collect</h2>
                <p>The site uses three categories of tools that touch visitor data:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Analytics (Google Analytics 4 + Microsoft Clarity):</strong>
                        page views, referrer, device class, interaction events
                        (<code>bh_cv_download</code>, <code>bh_linkedin_click</code>,
                        <code>bh_web_vital</code>, <code>bh_scroll_depth</code>). No personally identifying information.
                        Clarity records anonymous session replays with text and form fields masked by default.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Server-side event log (<code>/api/log-event.php</code>):</strong>
                        a same-origin failover that stores the same event names as GA4, plus a
                        SHA-256 hash of your IP address. Used only when the client-side channel is blocked.
                        Retained for 30 days.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Contact &amp; booking forms (Web3Forms):</strong>
                        whatever you type — name, email, message. Routed to
                        <code>info@bogihorvath.com</code> via Web3Forms' relay (with internal CC for redundancy).
                        I don't store it anywhere else and I don't add you to any mailing list
                        (I don't have one).
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="reveal">
                <h2>Consent Mode</h2>
                <p>
                    The site implements <strong>Google Consent Mode v2 with granted defaults</strong>.
                    Analytics cookies are set on first visit unless you click "Reject" in the
                    consent banner. Your choice is stored in a first-party cookie
                    (<code>bh_cookie_consent</code>) for 365 days. Details of every cookie
                    and how to revoke consent are in the <a href="/cookies/">Cookie Policy</a>.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="reveal">
                <h2>Your rights (GDPR)</h2>
                <p>You can email me at <a href="{{ site.contact.emailHref }}">{{ site.contact.email }}</a> to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Request a copy of any data tied to your contact form submission.</li>
                    <li>Ask me to delete your form submission from my inbox.</li>
                    <li>Opt out of all analytics (or just use the consent banner's "Reject" option).</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    I respond to these under 24 hours on weekdays. For analytics data, I only
                    hold aggregate reports — there is no user-level record on my end because
                    GA4 stores pseudonymous IDs, not email addresses.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="reveal">
                <h2>Third-party sub-processors</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Google</strong> — Analytics + Tag Manager. Data may transfer to the US.</li>
                    <li><strong>Microsoft</strong> — Clarity session analytics. Data may transfer to the US.</li>
                    <li><strong>Web3Forms</strong> — form relay. Data routed to my inbox and not retained by them after delivery.</li>
                    <li><strong>Hostinger</strong> — web hosting. Standard server logs with IP retention per their policy.</li>
                    <li><strong>Cloudflare / cdnjs</strong> — asset CDN (fonts, icons).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="reveal">
                <h2>Changes</h2>
                <p>
                    When this policy changes, the "Last updated" date at the top will change.
                    Substantive changes will also be noted in the
                    <a href="/blog/">blog</a>. No retroactive changes to data handling will be applied
                    without a fresh banner.
                </p>
            </div>
